    {
        "id": 4,
        "type": "text",
        "name": null,
        "title": "How can you determine the right amount of product to hold as inventory?",
        "style": null,
        "decorator": null,
        "content": "<p>Getting the right amount of inventory when stocking is extremely important. Order too little and you&#39;re at risk of losing customers. Order too much and you might be stuck with extra stock that you&#39;ll be forced to sell at a big discount or have it expire; all while paying extra carrying costs.</p>\n\n<p>One way to go about deciding on a reordering amount is to use information from previous months. In this case, you need to have the right inventory data at hand. A smart choice here would be to get a solution that will automatically track your inventory fluctuations. Even if you chose to go a slightly different route and use inventory forecasting software or even just Excel, you&#39;re still going to need inventory information from the previous months.</p>\n",
        "url": null,
        "noTop": null,
        "noBottom": true,
        "noPad": null
    },
    {
        "id": 5,
        "type": "image-with-text",
