        "title": "How to set the reorder point for new inventory",
        "style": "dark",
        "contentBefore": "",
        "items": [
            {
                "text": "<p>The next important point you need to calculate is the right time to place your order for inventory restocking. EOQ answers the question of &quot;What is an inventory level you want to maintain?&quot;, but it doesn&#39;t tell you how to actually restock. Ideally, you want your restock shipment to arrive when your previous batch is about to sell out. If it comes too early, you might face all kinds of storage and handling issues. And if it comes late, you&#39;re in danger of running out of stock. So, you want to make sure you always have enough products, which is where determining your reorder point gets important.</p>\n"
            },
